column37: 9,000euros foal; fifth foal; sister to the stable's Basford (RPR 117) who won a bumper at 7-2 on debut; dam (129) also won a bumper on debut; yard 1-1 in bumpers this season; interesting on debut, especially if backed.

column37: Two-time point winner who was bought for £50,000 in May; 11-1 when 10l fifth of nine on last month's bumper debut at Uttoxeter (2m, good) and that looked a warm race (winner was a Listed runner-up next time); player.

column36: Initial promise in early summer before disappointing; back from a break and gelded
column37: Won Naas barrier trial and shaped well on rules debut when fourth in Curragh maiden over this trip in June; out of depth but still well below that form both starts afterwards, in Naas Listed and last of 4 in Group 3 Tyros Stakes (jockey reported him to take a false step and not travel afterwards); gelded since and back from a break with Robson de Aguiar having taken over the licence from Adrian Murray; draw not ideal.
